[White "1. Typical Tricks & Traps"]
[Black "Foreword"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 e5
{ Since World Champion Magnus Carlsen implemented the Sveshnikov Sicilian into his repertoire during his title match against Fabiano Caruana, this opening experiences a renaissance. Time to check out typical tactics.   Learning an opening isn't just memorizing variations and understanding the general strategical ideas. In our opinion, you best amplify your knowledge in openings and structures by internalizing the common tactical motifs. This book gives you an overview of the most typical tactics in the Sveshnikov Sicilian from both the White and the Black side. By learning them you will not only sometimes win a game effortlessly or stop a tactical idea from your opponent you weren't aware of, but you'll also strongly strengthen your understanding of typical Sveshnikov positions. If you try to understand why and when a certain tactic works, where the typically strong and weak points are and which pieces might be in danger, you will learn how to set up your pieces harmoniously.   There are two entry chapters with simple puzzles, and then five thematic chapters. After these almost 100 exercises, you can test your fresh skills in three test chapters of increasing average difficulty which consist of 15 positions each. Finally, for the fearless, there is a bonus chapter with extremely hard puzzles.   A few words on our approach to finding good and interesting positions. We've developed technology and sophisticated algorithms to automatically find correct and interesting puzzles for various topics. We handpick the best ones and refine the solutions. That means these puzzles are carefully selected by their relevance and cover all frequently occurring tactics. All puzzles have a clear and carefully checked solution.   Enjoy ! }
*

