{ This chapter deals with tactics in the center. In the Sveshnikov, control of the d5-square is crucial. White tries to exploit its weakness by putting a dominant knight there or by using it as an operational square for the queen from where it can attack on the light squares. On the other hand, Black sometimes can open the center to his advantage with a timely d5. }
