1... e4
{ This idea is very important in this structure and must be remembered. Black frees the e5-square for one of his pieces, in this case the bishop. }
2. fxe4 Be5
{ The positional   19...f4  is often an idea, but here White can counter with the typical  20.e5 !   20.Qe2 ?  is what Black would be looking for  (Be5 ! -+)  followed by a very strong attack on the kingside. Look at White's sad pieces.  20...Bxe5  21.Bxh7+  Kh8  22.Qg6  += }
3. exf5 { 20.Kh1  Qh6  21.g3  f4  -+  is crushing } 3... Bxh2+
{ White's king doesn't find shelter on neither the h- nor the f-file. } *

